How to contribute:

In this archive there is a file called A_Template.guide, just fill in each of
the different nodes and such with the pertinent details.

Use the format of the existing files as a guideline of how to do everything.



Important contributors:

The .long files use smartwrap. For this to function each paragraph must be
followed by a @{PAR} + 2 newlines (as to make it compatible with older Amiga
guide versions).

Always fill a line until character 80, if a word goes beyond this, don't use a
hyphen (unless it is a word with a hyphen), but move the whole word to the
beginning of the next line.

If you are making links, write the paragraph first, when the paragraph is
correctly formatted, then insert the links. Use a space before the word and
after the word as this @{" LINK words " LINK "path"}.

If you are linking to other filetypes recognized by the datatype system,
remember to write the complete path of the file, the files name followed by
/main, which let's the datatypes and AmigaGuide decide how to use the link.

When in doubt look at the examples.

After you have created your own monster send it to me for future inclusion.



